I'm not in Belgium to be jailbait!
Watch it!

509
00:40:15,119 --> 00:40:16,579
Don't do that again!

510
00:40:16,750 --> 00:40:19,579
I just wanted to see
how he was doing.

511
00:40:20,750 --> 00:40:23,619
- Shit, I almost shot him!
- OK, sit down!

512
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:30,840
Robbing a bank in Belgium
can't be that hard!

513
00:40:31,010 --> 00:40:33,469
Shit! What are we
gonna do now?

514
00:40:34,099 --> 00:40:36,639
Leave now, while
you still can.

515
00:40:37,929 --> 00:40:39,309
- He's right!
- Shut up!

516
00:40:41,150 --> 00:40:42,389
Turn yourselves in.

517
00:40:42,559 --> 00:40:46,309
In any case, we all saw
the gunshot was an accident.

518
00:40:46,489 --> 00:40:49,570
If I want some stretching tips,
I'll call you.

519
00:40:50,699 --> 00:40:51,610
Well done!

520
00:40:52,030 --> 00:40:55,699
You can insult me all you want
or even hit a hostage,

521
00:40:55,869 --> 00:40:57,530
but I'm not
turning myself in!

522
00:40:58,289 --> 00:40:59,909
We gotta block the exits.

523
00:41:00,619 --> 00:41:03,289
You keep an eye on them
and cut the crap!

524
00:41:03,460 --> 00:41:06,079
You're saying that
a man broke in...

525
00:41:06,710 --> 00:41:09,880
and then you say
he got in with a key!

526
00:41:10,050 --> 00:41:12,760
We gotta be clear
on this one,

527
00:41:13,139 --> 00:41:16,050
otherwise,
it'll be a false statement.

528
00:41:16,969 --> 00:41:18,519
If you say he was drunk,

529
00:41:18,679 --> 00:41:22,929
I won't know for sure
until the alcohol test has been done.

530
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:25,059
It's as simple as that.

531
00:41:25,269 --> 00:41:27,429
Boss, guess who's robbing
the post office!

532
00:41:27,610 --> 00:41:28,389
Who?

533
00:41:29,440 --> 00:41:32,610
I liked how you pressured
the hostages earlier.

534
00:41:32,780 --> 00:41:34,280
It wasn't for them.

535
00:41:34,949 --> 00:41:37,110
You heard Karate Kid.
If we cooperate...

536
00:41:37,289 --> 00:41:38,739
Listen up, brainiac.

537
00:41:39,079 --> 00:41:40,989
Who said it was a
perfect plan,

538
00:41:41,159 --> 00:41:43,619
that post offices
are like the Red Cross,

539
00:41:43,789 --> 00:41:45,500
and that we'd catch
the 12:43 train?

540
00:41:45,670 --> 00:41:46,530
But, the moron...

541
00:41:46,710 --> 00:41:49,289
The moron's your pal,
not mine.

542
00:41:49,460 --> 00:41:51,750
So, if you wanna be
the boss...

543
00:42:07,820 --> 00:42:10,940
If you wanna be the boss
and keep giving orders,

544
00:42:11,150 --> 00:42:14,400
you'd better start growin' some balls
otherwise, I'm taking over.

545
00:42:14,570 --> 00:42:17,280
And I don't mind
getting my hands dirty.

546
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:30,760
Commissioner! Please!

547
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:32,960
Hey, it's
Commissioner Bruges!

548
00:42:33,130 --> 00:42:35,090
Is Van Damme the perp?

549
00:42:35,260 --> 00:42:36,800
Wait. No declaration yet.

550
00:42:36,969 --> 00:42:38,349
Has anyone been shot?

551
00:42:40,429 --> 00:42:42,840
How many hostages
are held inside?

552
00:42:46,099 --> 00:42:48,010
- Enough.
- What's your plan?

553
00:42:48,190 --> 00:42:50,230
No, please!
Get him outta here!

554
00:42:54,820 --> 00:42:56,199
Be careful with the seats.

555
00:42:58,409 --> 00:43:02,409
Careful! You know how much
I can sell it for on eBay?

556
00:43:11,380 --> 00:43:13,340
No, nothing's moving.

557
00:43:14,340 --> 00:43:16,000
Can he turn that off?

558
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:19,050
- The whining thing?
- The nerves.

559
00:43:23,309 --> 00:43:24,889
- Is that him?
- Yes.

560
00:43:25,349 --> 00:43:27,010
Did he dye his hair?

561
00:43:42,369 --> 00:43:43,739
He's in shock.

562
00:43:44,710 --> 00:43:47,030
- What?
- He's still in shock.

563
00:43:47,369 --> 00:43:49,869
Once in the film
"Hard Target",

564
00:43:50,039 --> 00:43:52,289
I took a shot from a blank.

565
00:43:52,460 --> 00:43:54,920
It took salts to
reanimate me.

566
00:43:55,260 --> 00:43:57,880
"Hard Target"! John Woo!

567
00:43:58,050 --> 00:44:00,039
- What an ass!
- Don't say that!

568
00:44:00,219 --> 00:44:02,460
C'mon, Jean-Claude,
wait a sec!

569
00:44:02,639 --> 00:44:04,719
He's the one who brought him
to the US.

570
00:44:04,889 --> 00:44:08,969
Without him, he'd still be
filming pigeons in Hong Kong!

571
00:44:09,349 --> 00:44:11,760
And then what?
He drops you!

572
00:44:12,820 --> 00:44:14,969
At least, he did "Face Off".

573
00:44:15,150 --> 00:44:17,559
So what?
He could have picked you!

574
00:44:18,409 --> 00:44:22,980
On the other hand, when you see
"Windtalkers", there's a justice...

575
00:44:23,989 --> 00:44:25,570
Got any new projects?

576
00:44:26,039 --> 00:44:27,449
Not for now.

577
00:44:27,619 --> 00:44:30,659
I saw a thing on the web,
what's it called?

578
00:44:32,670 --> 00:44:34,789
Purple.
"Purple Amulet".

579
00:44:36,340 --> 00:44:37,539
What about it?

580
00:44:37,800 --> 00:44:40,130
- Steven Seagal got the part.
- What?

581
00:44:40,300 --> 00:44:41,579
He got the part.

582
00:44:41,760 --> 00:44:42,679
Steven Seagal?

583
00:44:42,849 --> 00:44:44,550
You're ten times better!

584
00:44:47,309 --> 00:44:49,469
Well, he cut off his couette.

585
00:44:49,639 --> 00:44:50,969
His what?

586
00:44:51,150 --> 00:44:52,340
His couette.

587
00:44:53,730 --> 00:44:55,309
His ponytail!

588
00:44:55,900 --> 00:44:57,230
For the first time!

589
00:44:57,610 --> 00:45:00,070
Oh, I see...
That's a tough one...

590
00:45:02,659 --> 00:45:05,280
Hey you! What's that?
What are you doing?

591
00:45:05,789 --> 00:45:07,070
- Me?
- Yeah, you!

592
00:45:07,250 --> 00:45:08,699
- Hey!
- He coughed.

593
00:45:08,869 --> 00:45:10,250
No. You're disturbing us!

594
00:45:10,420 --> 00:45:11,739
I think he just coughed.

595
00:45:12,170 --> 00:45:14,039
- He coughed!
- Think I'm funny?

596
00:45:14,210 --> 00:45:16,250
- No.
- You think I'm funny!

597
00:45:16,420 --> 00:45:17,829
No.

598
00:45:18,010 --> 00:45:20,409
- Oh, is he funny?
- No.

599
00:45:20,590 --> 00:45:23,460
So, I see.
It's the 'aware' thing, is that it?

600
00:45:23,929 --> 00:45:25,590
- Who are you?
- Drop it.

601
00:45:25,760 --> 00:45:28,639
No, wait!
Who do you think you are?

602
00:45:28,809 --> 00:45:32,059
You're 40
and still wearing sweatshirts?

603
00:45:32,230 --> 00:45:33,010
Yeah.

604
00:45:33,190 --> 00:45:34,679
Who do you think you are?

605
00:45:35,480 --> 00:45:37,849
No, no, no! Shut up, OK?

606
00:45:38,360 --> 00:45:40,440
He's tired, you know.
Drop it.

607
00:45:40,610 --> 00:45:41,639
- Tired?
- Yeah.

608
00:45:41,820 --> 00:45:44,530
I'm not tired, are you?
No, you're not.

609
00:45:44,909 --> 00:45:46,980
So, shut up!

610
00:45:49,199 --> 00:45:51,739
Get up.
Yeah get up, now!

611
00:45:55,340 --> 00:45:57,579
- Got a smoke?
- I don't smoke.

612
00:45:59,090 --> 00:46:00,670
Does anyone have a smoke?

613
00:46:26,159 --> 00:46:28,530
- So?
- It's ringing, but no answer.

614
00:46:29,039 --> 00:46:30,610
- No one?
- Nope.

615
00:46:31,409 --> 00:46:32,789
Forget it, then.

616
00:46:33,000 --> 00:46:36,869
Go get me a screamo-phone,
like they use in movies.

617
00:46:37,380 --> 00:46:39,119
To shout at the public.

618
00:46:39,300 --> 00:46:41,420
The day had started out fine!

619
00:46:41,590 --> 00:46:45,460
But now, I'm exhausted, I'm fed up.
I got scared!

620
00:46:46,090 --> 00:46:47,889
- Sir, let's stop...
- Do I know you?

621
00:46:48,059 --> 00:46:49,050
I'm Commissioner Bruges.

622
00:46:49,219 --> 00:46:51,929
Sir, I'm freaking out!

623
00:46:52,179 --> 00:46:53,809
There's been a hold-up

624
00:46:53,980 --> 00:46:55,769
across the street...

625
00:46:55,940 --> 00:46:57,429
But look at my cab!

626
00:46:57,940 --> 00:47:01,889
That's what I'm saying,
let's proceed 'step by step'.

627
00:47:02,070 --> 00:47:03,179
Look at my cab!

628
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:04,360
A few questions, first.

629
00:47:04,570 --> 00:47:07,280
I picked him up at
the airport.

630
00:47:07,949 --> 00:47:10,570
Did he have any
luggage, ma'am?

631
00:47:11,750 --> 00:47:12,690
Man, I can't.

632
00:47:12,869 --> 00:47:15,110
Please! Only once!

633
00:47:15,619 --> 00:47:16,570
I don't want to.

634
00:47:18,210 --> 00:47:19,210
Open your mouth.

635
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:23,000
Be cool, just once!

636
00:47:23,170 --> 00:47:24,500
I'm exhausted.

637
00:47:24,679 --> 00:47:27,550
Do me a favor!
I might never see you again.

638
00:47:27,719 --> 00:47:31,500
Show me the move,
just once, please! Go ahead!

639
00:47:32,139 --> 00:47:33,800
Please, Jean-Claude!

640
00:47:49,239 --> 00:47:50,489
Let's all applaud!

641
00:47:56,289 --> 00:47:57,619
Nice, Jean-Claude!

642
00:47:58,380 --> 00:48:01,250
Told you he was the best!
Where are you going?

643
00:48:01,460 --> 00:48:03,750
Who told you to move?
Get back there.

644
00:48:03,920 --> 00:48:04,920
Faster!

645
00:48:06,969 --> 00:48:08,380
Where's my ciggy?

646
00:48:13,099 --> 00:48:14,179
Open your mouth!

647
00:48:28,780 --> 00:48:30,159
Move back a bit.

648
00:48:30,619 --> 00:48:31,780
A bit lower.

649
00:48:36,710 --> 00:48:37,739
- Jean-Claude?
- Yeah?

650
00:48:37,909 --> 00:48:39,539
- It's been years...
- So, don't do it.

651
00:48:40,750 --> 00:48:41,619
Just once!

652
00:48:51,889 --> 00:48:55,389
He shows up and says "Go!".
So off I went with him.

653
00:48:55,559 --> 00:48:56,389
He said that?

654
00:48:56,559 --> 00:48:58,300
Yes, sir.

655
00:48:58,480 --> 00:49:01,150
I did what he told me to,
he's a big star!

656
00:49:06,860 --> 00:49:08,690
- What's this?
- I just fell!

657
00:49:08,860 --> 00:49:10,190
And what are you doing?

658
00:49:10,820 --> 00:49:12,019
Come here now!

659
00:49:13,949 --> 00:49:15,940
- He needs a doc.
- Are you a nurse?

660
00:49:16,619 --> 00:49:18,199
Mr Van Damme!

661
00:49:18,869 --> 00:49:19,949
This is...

662
00:49:20,170 --> 00:49:23,079
Commissioner Bruges,
pick up the phone

663
00:49:23,250 --> 00:49:24,579
so we can talk.

664
00:49:25,250 --> 00:49:26,329
Is this a joke?

665
00:49:27,130 --> 00:49:28,539
No, Jean-Claude.

666
00:49:29,260 --> 00:49:31,170
They saw you with
the cabinet.

667
00:49:31,639 --> 00:49:34,639
- Moving a cabinet is robbing a bank?
- Shut up!

668
00:49:34,809 --> 00:49:38,219
If you need anything,
pick up the phone.

669
00:49:39,849 --> 00:49:41,969
I'm your contact.

670
00:49:43,059 --> 00:49:44,389
Bruges.

671
00:49:47,610 --> 00:49:49,440
Here's our ticket out!

672
00:49:50,949 --> 00:49:52,519
I have enough problems...

673
00:49:52,699 --> 00:49:54,320
I said, shut up!

674
00:49:57,789 --> 00:49:58,699
Go ahead, big shot!

675
00:50:08,800 --> 00:50:10,869
Are we having fun, here?

676
00:50:14,139 --> 00:50:15,000
Can't believe it!

677
00:50:26,059 --> 00:50:27,809
- You read English?
- Yes.

678
00:50:39,329 --> 00:50:42,489
If you tell them,
you'll have blood on your hands.

679
00:50:44,329 --> 00:50:46,539
- What do I say?
- Let them talk.

680
00:50:48,500 --> 00:50:49,500
What's "custody"?

681
00:50:49,670 --> 00:50:51,550
He picked up!

682
00:50:56,469 --> 00:50:57,420
Mr Van Damme.

683
00:51:00,309 --> 00:51:02,380
Bruges. How's it
going inside?

684
00:51:06,230 --> 00:51:07,769
It could be better.

685
00:51:09,019 --> 00:51:11,889
OK, let me ask you first,
is anyone injured?

686
00:51:17,530 --> 00:51:19,079
A man's unconscious
and bleeding.

687
00:51:20,409 --> 00:51:22,530
OK, good.
May I call you Jean-Claude?

688
00:51:23,619 --> 00:51:24,869
I'm Commissioner Bruges.

689
00:51:25,670 --> 00:51:27,239
You can call me Christian.

690
00:51:28,630 --> 00:51:30,920
You must release
the wounded man.

691
00:51:31,130 --> 00:51:34,550
Neither one of us
wants to have blood on our hands.

692
00:51:34,760 --> 00:51:35,619
Of course.

693
00:51:35,969 --> 00:51:37,630
Will you release him?

694
00:51:40,099 --> 00:51:42,929
No, no one leaves.
It's impossible.

695
00:51:50,400 --> 00:51:52,190
What if I came with a doctor?

696
00:51:56,150 --> 00:52:00,019
Hey, if there's a murder,
it's no longer a robbery.

697
00:52:04,909 --> 00:52:07,320
- And if I come with a doc?
- Alright, but unarmed.

698
00:52:08,130 --> 00:52:09,409
I give you my word.

699
00:52:09,630 --> 00:52:10,460
Bruges...

700
00:52:13,460 --> 00:52:16,219
- Whoever walks in is dead.
- If a man dies, we're screwed.

701
00:52:16,380 --> 00:52:17,300
Heard me earlier?

702
00:52:19,090 --> 00:52:21,170
Well, they could come naked.

703
00:52:22,260 --> 00:52:25,800
In hostage movies, the bad guys
ask the good guys to come in

704
00:52:25,980 --> 00:52:28,269
naked, so they know
they're clean.

705
00:52:29,150 --> 00:52:30,559
How about naked?

706
00:52:36,900 --> 00:52:38,019
Fine, tell them.

707
00:53:03,510 --> 00:53:04,380
Where's Petrucciani?

708
00:53:06,980 --> 00:53:08,429
3. Stone falls on Egg,

709
00:53:08,599 --> 00:53:11,349
Egg breaks.

710
00:53:34,090 --> 00:53:36,869
Hey, Jean-Claude, excuse me!
Didn't recognize you!

711
00:53:41,969 --> 00:53:43,130
Speak.

712
00:53:43,429 --> 00:53:44,460
Hey, Jeff. How are you?

713
00:53:45,099 --> 00:53:46,559
Hey, dawg!
What's up, dawg?

714
00:53:47,519 --> 00:53:49,559
Good, good, good...
Not so good.

715
00:53:49,730 --> 00:53:51,099
I need some money.

716
00:53:51,269 --> 00:53:52,880
Listen,
can you advance, er...

717
00:53:52,889 --> 00:53:55,050
Can the producers
advance me some money?

718
00:53:55,230 --> 00:53:58,519
Listen, Jean-Claude,
I was gonna call you...

719
00:53:58,739 --> 00:54:00,280
...right after your
vacation was over.

720
00:54:00,449 --> 00:54:02,570
They took
somebody else.

721
00:54:02,739 --> 00:54:03,820
Who?

722
00:54:04,239 --> 00:54:05,320
Steven.

723
00:54:05,489 --> 00:54:07,030
Steven?

724
00:54:07,659 --> 00:54:10,230
He promised to cut off
his ponytail.

725
00:54:11,250 --> 00:54:12,239
I know it hurts,

726
00:54:12,460 --> 00:54:13,539
I know it.

727
00:54:14,039 --> 00:54:16,829
Ok, ok, can you... Can I borrow
some money from you?

728
00:54:18,710 --> 00:54:20,670
Hello!
You're breaking up...

729
00:54:23,139 --> 00:54:25,460
Hey, man! You're breaking
up here, I'm losing you.

730
00:54:26,219 --> 00:54:28,179
You must be in a
tunnel or something!

731
00:54:28,429 --> 00:54:30,550
Cut the bullshit!
Come on the phone!

732
00:54:31,829 --> 00:54:33,320
All right.
Yeah, yeah.

733
00:54:33,980 --> 00:54:35,059
What's next?

734
00:54:35,230 --> 00:54:38,349
No Limit Injury.
It's about a Viet vet...

735
00:54:38,530 --> 00:54:39,940
We've done this
movie 6 months ago.

736
00:54:40,400 --> 00:54:41,570
We did?

737
00:54:41,739 --> 00:54:42,650
What's next?

738
00:54:42,860 --> 00:54:47,110
No Limit Injury 2!
It's about a Gulf War vet

739
00:54:47,280 --> 00:54:50,650
who fights to pay
for his son's education.

740
00:54:52,159 --> 00:54:54,409
- Is it good?
- I don't know.

741
00:54:55,460 --> 00:54:57,539
- Did you read it?
- I don't know.

742
00:55:03,630 --> 00:55:08,429
Call the producers... and...
tell them I need some money up front.

743
00:55:08,889 --> 00:55:12,159
- Hey, man, I can't do that!
- Just fucking do it, Jeff!

744
00:55:17,440 --> 00:55:19,400
Aren't you Van Damme?

745
00:55:20,400 --> 00:55:23,190
You're Jean-Claude Van Damme,
my idol!

746
00:55:23,360 --> 00:55:24,309
Listen...

747
00:55:26,449 --> 00:55:28,570
I'm really tired and I...

748
00:55:29,030 --> 00:55:32,070
Don't start acting
like a big shot,

749
00:55:32,949 --> 00:55:35,159
Mr Hero of the century!

750
00:55:35,329 --> 00:55:39,579
I can finally talk to you
and listen to that tone!

751
00:55:39,750 --> 00:55:43,250
Let me talk to you.
You can rest, but let me talk.

752
00:55:43,420 --> 00:55:46,130
Close your eyes,
but let me talk to you.

753
00:55:46,300 --> 00:55:49,719
Anyway, when I see
you on screen,

754
00:55:49,889 --> 00:55:52,639
well, you're really
different!

755
00:55:52,809 --> 00:55:53,510
Really?

756
00:55:53,679 --> 00:55:56,440
I think you look much better
on screen.

757
00:55:56,599 --> 00:55:58,980
And you're much nicer too,

758
00:55:59,150 --> 00:56:01,019
I can tell you that...

759
00:56:01,190 --> 00:56:03,679
- No, it's just that...
- Even if you're tired.

760
00:56:04,780 --> 00:56:06,980
I like you better on screen.

761
00:56:07,159 --> 00:56:09,780
- You hurt my feelings.
- Oh, c'mon...

762
00:56:09,949 --> 00:56:13,369
I always thought
you'd be nicer.

763
00:56:13,539 --> 00:56:17,750
Everyone worships you
here in Belgium, you're our star!

764
00:56:17,920 --> 00:56:20,409
You represent us
in Hollywood.

765
00:56:20,710 --> 00:56:23,119
Get used to having a driver
who talks!

766
00:56:23,300 --> 00:56:23,909
OK.

767
00:56:24,090 --> 00:56:25,420
- Please!
- Sorry.

768
00:56:25,590 --> 00:56:27,500
Yes, sorry! Yes!

769
00:56:27,969 --> 00:56:29,000
What's that?

770
00:56:30,349 --> 00:56:32,500
You don't need to show off!

771
00:56:33,389 --> 00:56:36,809
- You're doing it on purpose or what?
- No, I'm not.

772
00:56:39,019 --> 00:56:40,219
But you're nice.

773
00:56:40,860 --> 00:56:43,010
You too, but even
more on screen!

774
00:56:43,320 --> 00:56:44,429
It's hot in here!

775
00:56:44,610 --> 00:56:46,440
- Should I open?
- No, I'm tired.

776
00:56:46,610 --> 00:56:48,980
Then sleep, but let me talk.

777
00:56:49,159 --> 00:56:51,150
All cab drivers in
Brussels talk!

778
00:56:51,659 --> 00:56:55,280
You better get used to it
if you come here often.

779
00:56:57,039 --> 00:56:58,619
No, seriously!

780
00:56:59,460 --> 00:57:02,210
Star, star, star.
What are we talking about?

781
00:57:03,340 --> 00:57:06,539
I surely didn't expect
this kind of attitude!

782
00:57:06,719 --> 00:57:10,130
Ma'am, I didn't mean to...
Sorry.

783
00:57:10,300 --> 00:57:14,599
Well you hurt me anyway,
you don't realize, you're my idol!

784
00:57:14,769 --> 00:57:15,460
I'm sorry.

785
00:57:15,639 --> 00:57:17,969
I saw all your films.

786
00:57:18,139 --> 00:57:21,590
How can you be so rude?

787
00:57:21,769 --> 00:57:23,809
I'm sorry, I'm tired...

788
00:57:24,730 --> 00:57:27,730
- I still want a picture with you!
- I promise.

789
00:57:27,900 --> 00:57:29,280
- Promise?
- Yes, ma'am.

790
00:57:29,449 --> 00:57:31,320
- And you'll sign it?
- Yes, ma'am.

791
00:57:31,489 --> 00:57:33,150
- It's for my son!
- Yes, ma'am.

792
00:57:34,119 --> 00:57:35,909
Jean-Claude!

793
00:58:01,849 --> 00:58:05,639
It's been over an hour and a half now
since Van Damme

794
00:58:05,820 --> 00:58:08,900
has taken refuge in the Schaerbeek
downtown post office.

795
00:58:11,070 --> 00:58:12,860
She looks better on TV.

796
00:58:14,239 --> 00:58:16,699
We can't really say
what happened.

797
00:58:16,869 --> 00:58:19,739
After using a gun
several times,

798
00:58:19,909 --> 00:58:21,570
an anonymous source says...

799
00:58:21,750 --> 00:58:24,039
So tell the source
to stay anonymous!

800
00:58:25,710 --> 00:58:28,670
If anyone blabs,
you'll hear from me!

801
00:58:29,420 --> 00:58:30,670
Yes, chief.

802
00:58:32,429 --> 00:58:34,880
Thank you, chief.
Call him back.

803
00:58:38,059 --> 00:58:41,260
No, he was here
and there were three people there.

804
00:58:41,980 --> 00:58:45,389
OK, the Prefect authorized
the transfer. It's an order.

805
00:58:45,559 --> 00:58:46,679
And the ransom?

806
00:58:47,019 --> 00:58:49,349
- That'll have to calm him down.
- I've seen worse.

807
00:58:49,530 --> 00:58:52,730
There's no attack.
With a kid inside, I'm not budging.

808
00:58:55,949 --> 00:58:57,190
He picked up!

809
00:59:01,250 --> 00:59:01,949
Good news!

810
00:59:02,369 --> 00:59:05,079
- The transfer's authorized.
- Did it go through?

811
00:59:05,250 --> 00:59:06,199
It will

812
00:59:06,420 --> 00:59:09,539
if you cooperate...
Sorry, but it's a 2-way street.

813
00:59:11,719 --> 00:59:12,500
And the money?

814
00:59:12,880 --> 00:59:15,590
Same thing, it'll
take a bit longer.

815
00:59:15,889 --> 00:59:18,670
You're gonna have
to cooperate.

816
00:59:18,889 --> 00:59:20,050
It's...

817
00:59:20,219 --> 00:59:21,389
What do you want?

818
00:59:21,559 --> 00:59:23,389
The kid. Let him go.

819
00:59:28,480 --> 00:59:29,730
I'll call you back.

820
00:59:31,230 --> 00:59:35,699
The crowd's agitated.
Something's going on over there.

821
00:59:35,860 --> 00:59:36,809
What's the commotion?

822
00:59:36,989 --> 00:59:40,239
Let's go.
Despite all this confusion,

823
00:59:40,489 --> 00:59:42,150
a car is trying to
get through.

824
00:59:44,409 --> 00:59:45,329
- Who is it?
- What?

825
00:59:45,500 --> 00:59:46,869
- Who is it?
- The Van Varenbergs.

826
00:59:47,039 --> 00:59:48,619
- Who?
- Van Damme's parents.

827
00:59:48,789 --> 00:59:50,289
Why don't you escort them?

828
00:59:54,260 --> 00:59:56,050
Please! Please!

829
00:59:58,219 --> 00:59:59,960
Mrs Van Damme!
Your son...

830
01:00:01,219 --> 01:00:02,969
My son's a good man!

831
01:00:03,139 --> 01:00:04,139
No comment!

832
01:00:04,429 --> 01:00:07,969
What do you think you're doing?
Trying to screw me?

833
01:00:08,150 --> 01:00:11,150
- You're nuts or what?
- Say you wanna screw me.

834
01:00:11,320 --> 01:00:13,309
- I'm not saying that.
- The kid stays.

835
01:00:13,739 --> 01:00:16,610
- They gave in.
- Shut up. It's our only vest.

836
01:00:16,780 --> 01:00:18,190
He's right. They gave in.

837
01:00:18,369 --> 01:00:20,400
Hey, who's doing the hold-up?

838
01:00:20,579 --> 01:00:23,030
They gave in to him.
No hostage is leaving.

839
01:00:23,199 --> 01:00:25,110
Get back, I told you!

840
01:00:25,289 --> 01:00:27,329
For the second
time, don't move!

841
01:00:27,500 --> 01:00:28,659
- Watch your tone.
- I do as I please.

842
01:00:28,829 --> 01:00:30,869
- Get on back!
- Shut up, you heard me.

843
01:00:31,800 --> 01:00:33,340
- Lower your gun.
- Calm down!

844
01:00:33,510 --> 01:00:35,130
You lower yours first.

845
01:00:35,380 --> 01:00:37,670
- Go on back.
- Shut up and lower your gun.

846
01:00:37,969 --> 01:00:39,510
- Go on back.
- I'm going now.

847
01:00:39,679 --> 01:00:41,590
They'll break negotiations.

848
01:00:42,639 --> 01:00:44,510
And I'll break your neck.

849
01:00:47,389 --> 01:00:50,019
If it's not the kid,
let a hostage go.

850
01:00:50,190 --> 01:00:52,230
Just don't shoot, man.

851
01:00:53,650 --> 01:00:54,679
Don't shoot.

852
01:00:55,690 --> 01:00:56,889
Stop it.

853
01:00:57,449 --> 01:00:58,480
He's right.

854
01:01:00,739 --> 01:01:02,610
If we let one go,
he's gonna talk.

855
01:01:03,409 --> 01:01:05,320
Not the one I'm thinking of.

856
01:01:47,659 --> 01:01:49,070
Tell them we'll release one.

857
01:01:49,250 --> 01:01:51,869
- Your maniac son hurt someone.
- Maniac?

858
01:01:54,170 --> 01:01:55,710
He's Jean-Claude.

859
01:01:55,960 --> 01:01:57,590
He's Camille.

860
01:01:57,920 --> 01:01:59,329
He's Franois.

861
01:01:59,590 --> 01:02:01,920
He's Van Damme or
Van Varenberg!

862
01:02:02,590 --> 01:02:04,420
But he's not a maniac!

863
01:02:09,309 --> 01:02:10,219
Get outta here.

864
01:02:14,110 --> 01:02:15,650
He's on the line, boss.

865
01:02:19,070 --> 01:02:20,309
Gotta do something
for the kid.

866
01:02:23,280 --> 01:02:25,739
Help me convince your son
to let him go.

867
01:02:33,960 --> 01:02:36,329
OK for a hostage,
but not the kid.

868
01:02:39,050 --> 01:02:40,510
Someone wants to talk to you.

869
01:02:46,929 --> 01:02:48,010
Honey?

870
01:02:49,639 --> 01:02:50,760
Mom?

871
01:02:53,440 --> 01:02:56,059
What are you doing, son?

872
01:02:56,980 --> 01:02:58,309
Nothing.

873
01:02:58,940 --> 01:02:59,860
Nothing!

874
01:03:01,360 --> 01:03:03,400
Please talk to me, dear.

875
01:03:04,030 --> 01:03:04,809
Nothing, mom.

876
01:03:06,829 --> 01:03:07,659
Mom, give me the...

877
01:03:07,869 --> 01:03:09,150
son of a bitch!

878
01:03:10,750 --> 01:03:12,539
Get my lawyer on the phone.

879
01:03:13,369 --> 01:03:17,039
Tell them I'm releasing a hostage.
Don't cry, Mom.

880
01:03:21,590 --> 01:03:22,920
Hurry up!

881
01:03:27,760 --> 01:03:29,010
Take them away.

882
01:03:38,900 --> 01:03:40,059
It was my mother.

883
01:03:41,230 --> 01:03:43,110
I don't give a shit
about your mother.

884
01:03:44,570 --> 01:03:46,559
Wanna hear about mine?

885
01:03:46,949 --> 01:03:49,190
- Last time I saw her...
- What?

886
01:03:49,789 --> 01:03:51,110
...was when I was born.

887
01:03:53,960 --> 01:03:56,360
He tries to screw me,
then he makes me cry.

888
01:03:56,710 --> 01:03:59,030
You come with me.

889
01:03:59,880 --> 01:04:02,170
- Why?
- 'Cause you're getting out.

890
01:04:04,050 --> 01:04:04,960
So, let's go.

891
01:04:05,130 --> 01:04:06,929
No, he stays here.

892
01:04:07,090 --> 01:04:07,920
C'mon, mister.

893
01:04:08,139 --> 01:04:11,170
Make the transfer
and get me his lawyer.

894
01:04:15,190 --> 01:04:16,849
Rule number 1.

895
01:04:17,480 --> 01:04:19,800
It's the maniac
that shows good faith.

896
01:04:21,610 --> 01:04:22,889
C'mon.

897
01:04:25,949 --> 01:04:26,980
C'mon.

898
01:04:32,079 --> 01:04:34,860
- Why do I have to go?
- Shut up. Come with me.

899
01:04:35,039 --> 01:04:36,869
Why do you want to keep him?

900
01:04:37,170 --> 01:04:40,449
- He stays here. You come with me.
- Let him go.

901
01:04:41,250 --> 01:04:42,500
Not without me.

902
01:04:42,840 --> 01:04:45,670
Not without my son!

903
01:04:59,019 --> 01:04:59,969
Hello?

904
01:05:00,230 --> 01:05:02,469
Wait.
The lawyer's on the line.

905
01:05:06,820 --> 01:05:08,449
Hi, Sir.

906
01:05:08,699 --> 01:05:10,650
Mister...

907
01:05:11,780 --> 01:05:12,860
One moment...

908
01:05:13,949 --> 01:05:15,150
Mr. Bernstein,

909
01:05:16,329 --> 01:05:19,000
We need you to talk the voice
of reason to your client.

910
01:05:19,170 --> 01:05:20,119
Get him on the phone!

911
01:05:20,289 --> 01:05:21,670
Stand up, up you go!

912
01:05:23,630 --> 01:05:24,869
Let me go!

913
01:05:27,380 --> 01:05:29,420
- You sure are lucky.
- So are you.

914
01:05:29,590 --> 01:05:31,800
- With your gun.
- You too sure are lucky.

915
01:05:32,760 --> 01:05:34,420
You're really lucky.

916
01:05:40,980 --> 01:05:43,139
Let me go!

917
01:05:47,239 --> 01:05:50,190
Damien, I'll be back.
Mommy's coming back!

918
01:05:53,869 --> 01:05:54,900
Move.

919
01:06:01,789 --> 01:06:03,579
Move. Get up.

920
01:06:05,000 --> 01:06:06,909
When I say get up,
you get up!

921
01:06:07,300 --> 01:06:08,460
One word
and you're dead.

922
01:06:09,340 --> 01:06:10,340
Hello?

923
01:06:10,550 --> 01:06:12,789
Jean-Claude, what the hell
is wrong with you?

924
01:06:13,179 --> 01:06:14,510
Did you get the money?

925
01:06:14,679 --> 01:06:16,340
Yes, of course, but...
What the fuck...

926
01:06:16,719 --> 01:06:19,260
Okay then, do your job!

927
01:06:21,980 --> 01:06:25,889
If you open your mouth,
you're gonna find your kid in pieces.

928
01:06:27,190 --> 01:06:28,469
I'll take care of him.

929
01:06:30,280 --> 01:06:34,150
What? You can't even take care
of your own kid!

930
01:06:34,320 --> 01:06:35,610
It's all your fault!

931
01:06:35,829 --> 01:06:37,199
They're raising the curtain!

932
01:07:14,030 --> 01:07:15,610
Stand back.

933
01:07:16,869 --> 01:07:19,989
Please, ma'am.
I said stand back.

934
01:07:38,599 --> 01:07:39,840
Over there.

935
01:07:41,730 --> 01:07:43,599
Over there, I said.

936
01:07:47,769 --> 01:07:49,429
OK, so we put it
all in boxes.

937
01:07:49,610 --> 01:07:52,230
I'm gonna keep
a Christmas decoration.

938
01:07:52,400 --> 01:07:53,570
I like this one.

939
01:07:53,739 --> 01:07:55,280
It's a little beauty.

940
01:07:55,449 --> 01:07:59,989
This way, we'll remember
it's almost Mardi Gras.

941
01:08:00,159 --> 01:08:04,320
Our minds crossed.
I took a heart from my tree.

942
01:08:04,750 --> 01:08:09,460
Yeah, and St. Valentine's Day
is coming up. Hurray for love.

943
01:08:09,670 --> 01:08:10,619
Dimitri's so romantic!

944
01:08:10,800 --> 01:08:13,500
It's our 1,500th show today!

945
01:08:22,560 --> 01:08:24,350
This movie is for me.

946
01:08:26,520 --> 01:08:28,390
There we are, you and me.

947
01:08:36,569 --> 01:08:38,479
Why did you do that?

948
01:08:38,989 --> 01:08:41,560
Or why did I do that?

949
01:08:42,699 --> 01:08:44,529
You made my dream come true.

950
01:08:44,710 --> 01:08:46,529
I asked you for it.

951
01:08:46,750 --> 01:08:50,750
I promised you something in return
and I haven't delivered yet.

952
01:08:52,880 --> 01:08:55,960
You win, I lose.

953
01:08:58,390 --> 01:09:00,090
Unless...

954
01:09:00,720 --> 01:09:04,050
the path you've set for me

955
01:09:04,220 --> 01:09:05,600
is full of hurdles

956
01:09:05,770 --> 01:09:10,010
where the answer
comes before the question.

957
01:09:10,189 --> 01:09:12,430
Yeah, I do that.

958
01:09:13,479 --> 01:09:15,939
Now I know why.

959
01:09:16,109 --> 01:09:20,060
It's the cure,
from what I've seen here.

960
01:09:20,619 --> 01:09:22,659
It all makes sense.

961
01:09:23,199 --> 01:09:26,489
It makes sense
to those who understand.

962
01:09:28,920 --> 01:09:30,869
So... America,

963
01:09:32,090 --> 01:09:33,960
poverty,

964
01:09:34,590 --> 01:09:37,000
stealing to eat...

965
01:09:37,510 --> 01:09:41,920
Stalking producers,
actors, 'movie stars',

966
01:09:42,390 --> 01:09:45,720
going to clubs
hoping to see a star,

967
01:09:45,890 --> 01:09:49,090
with my pictures,
karate magazines.

968
01:09:49,270 --> 01:09:52,220
It's all I had.
I didn't speak English.

969
01:09:54,569 --> 01:09:57,270
But I did 20 years of karate.

970
01:09:57,439 --> 01:09:59,899
'Cause before I wasn't like that.

971
01:10:00,489 --> 01:10:02,699
This... This is me today.

972
01:10:02,869 --> 01:10:06,399
I used to be small
and scrawny.

973
01:10:06,579 --> 01:10:09,949
And I took up karate.
Hence the Dojo, hence respect,

974
01:10:10,119 --> 01:10:13,539
thou shall believe
people who say,

975
01:10:14,210 --> 01:10:15,369
"Oss!"

976
01:10:16,590 --> 01:10:18,050
It's Samurai code.

977
01:10:18,630 --> 01:10:20,340
It's honor, no lies.

978
01:10:20,510 --> 01:10:22,670
So this guy in the US,

979
01:10:23,050 --> 01:10:24,880
it's not the same thing.

980
01:10:25,220 --> 01:10:27,430
No one says "Oss" to you.

981
01:10:27,600 --> 01:10:31,300
Sometimes people
in show business say,

982
01:10:35,069 --> 01:10:38,399
I believed in
people, in the Dojo.

983
01:10:38,569 --> 01:10:42,779
I was blessed
and had a lot of 'wives'.

984
01:10:43,069 --> 01:10:45,279
I always believed in love.

985
01:10:45,579 --> 01:10:49,529
It's hard for a woman
with three kids to say,

986
01:10:49,710 --> 01:10:51,739
"Which one do I love more?"

987
01:10:51,920 --> 01:10:53,579
A mother...

988
01:10:54,130 --> 01:10:57,659
If you have 5, 6, 7
or 10 wives in a lifetime,

989
01:10:58,260 --> 01:11:00,960
they've all got
something special,

990
01:11:01,130 --> 01:11:03,010
but no one cares about that

991
01:11:03,180 --> 01:11:06,460
in the so-called media.

992
01:11:08,970 --> 01:11:10,470
What about drugs?

993
01:11:11,140 --> 01:11:14,100
When you got it all,
you travel the world.

994
01:11:14,859 --> 01:11:16,479
When you've been in
all the hotels,

995
01:11:16,649 --> 01:11:21,390
you're the prima donna
of the penthouse.

996
01:11:21,859 --> 01:11:25,529
And in all hotels the world over,
traveling,

997
01:11:25,699 --> 01:11:29,229
you want something more.

998
01:11:29,409 --> 01:11:31,399
And because of a woman...

999
01:11:31,579 --> 01:11:33,869
Well, because of love,

1000
01:11:34,039 --> 01:11:37,210
I tried something
and I got hooked.

1001
01:11:38,550 --> 01:11:41,829
Van Damme, the beast,

1002
01:11:42,090 --> 01:11:43,920
the tiger in a cage,

1003
01:11:44,090 --> 01:11:47,630
the "Bloodsport"
man got hooked.

1004
01:11:47,970 --> 01:11:51,890
I was wasted mentally
and physically.

1005
01:11:52,479 --> 01:11:56,010
To the point that
I got out of it.

1006
01:12:00,279 --> 01:12:02,069
I got out of it.

1007
01:12:03,399 --> 01:12:04,520
But...

1008
01:12:05,279 --> 01:12:07,239
It's all there.

1009
01:12:08,829 --> 01:12:10,649
It's all there.

1010
01:12:12,789 --> 01:12:14,779
It was really tough.

1011
01:12:17,170 --> 01:12:20,170
I saw people worse
off than me.

1012
01:12:20,340 --> 01:12:24,710
I went from poor to rich and thought,
why aren't we all like me.

1013
01:12:25,180 --> 01:12:26,970
Why all the privileges?

1014
01:12:27,140 --> 01:12:29,050
I'm just a regular guy.

1015
01:12:29,220 --> 01:12:31,590
It makes me sick to
see people...

1016
01:12:32,810 --> 01:12:34,720
who don't have what I've got.

1017
01:12:34,890 --> 01:12:36,800
Knowing that

1018
01:12:36,979 --> 01:12:40,390
they have qualities, too.

1019
01:12:40,569 --> 01:12:43,479
Much more than I do!

1020
01:12:43,649 --> 01:12:46,439
It's not my fault
if I was cut out to be a star.

1021
01:12:46,609 --> 01:12:48,439
I asked for it.

1022
01:12:48,619 --> 01:12:50,569
I asked for it,
really believed in it.

1023
01:12:50,739 --> 01:12:53,449
When you're 13,
you believe in your dream.

1024
01:12:53,619 --> 01:12:55,250
